snippet.textDisplay: A person can not be careful enough.  I am 81 and up until now, I only worry about getting it like everyone my age.  I wash my hands continually.  I spray the rooms and even some of the items I shop.  I still worry and try to be careful.  This morning I was really worried.  I awoke with a dry cough with whizzing,  used my prescribed proair hfa inhaler and after awhile felt better. I have only been out of my mobile once this week and that was to go to the local Walmart and get some food stuff.  I had a mouth mask but because I feel like 'Superman' didn't put it on .  No I am not superman, but just a jerk.  All I want to say is, be careful!! Don't listen to anybody but medical and scientific people.  Don't listen or follow any superman in  DC!
